name: Patti
description: Hello big world! When you're as little as I am, everything is big. And scary. See, I was a stray kitten who was taken in by a nice lady and when she took me to the vet for my spa day, her landlord found out and told her I wasn't allowed to come back. We were both heartbroken, but that's how I wound up here. It's way better than the streets, but I sure wish another nice lady (or man) would come along and give me another chance at having a home to call my own. If you contact Stephanie at (908) 331-0462 or stephanie@maarcadopt.org, she can arrange for us to meet, the sooner the better!

name: Charlie
description:
Some pets are in the Shelter and others in Foster homes.  Scroll thru description for preferred contact info!!

 Additionally for CATS you  may email latkinson@eulesstx.gov  and for DOGS, email trinitygapclub@gmail.com 

 

 

 


Meet Charlie! This gorgeous Great Pyrenees mix is one year old
and loves everyone he meets. Although young, he is calm for his age. He sat perfectly for his pictures and let all the GAP girls love on him.
He walks well on a leash and enjoys playing outside in the play yard. He is a fun easy dog and such fun to be with!
Sadly for Charlie, he lost his home when the owner could no longer keep him. Charlie is potty and kennel trained. This sweet boy needs a foster or forever home and will make a great addition to any home.
Charlie is now neutered, vaccinated, up to date on shots and heartworm negative. For more information on Charlie, please contact steffeniegaprescue@gmail.com

name: Dave
description: Dave is a social butterfly who loves to play and snuggle in close to his people, and has never met a human he didn't like. On top of being Mr. Popular, he'd also make a great candidate for Class Clown with his enthusiastic and playful nature. He loves to go on walks and romps with his friends at the shelter and then settle in for some serious cuddle time and scritches. Dave has lived in a home before and picked up some impressive manners. He walks nicely on leash, is fully house-trained and sleeps quietly through the night in his crate. He can also be left home without issue for eight-hour stretches. Although he hasn't lived with children, he has been noted to be playful, tolerant and easygoing with kids over the age of 6 that he's interacted with. He's lived successfully with a dog before, and as long as feeding time is properly managed, he should do okay with a well-matched doggie sibling. Dave is also in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Dave has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Dave is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told "free," coming when called and "Place", which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Dave will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Dave is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Dave after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https://vimeo.com/89434193 Obedient and eager to please, Dave would be a great fit for any number of loving homes. Come meet this sweet boy and see if he's perfect for yours!

name: Piper 11
description: Princess Piper is full of personality! This sweet girl is bold and silly, the first to greet you at the door and is always ready to play. She's full of energy. Piper doesn't sit still long enough to be considered a lap cat, but she does love using people as a playscape. Piper's an adorable puffball. Her hair stands on end and is so soft. She also has big eyes that will make you fall in love with her at a glance! Piper is super active and would love to go home with her brother, Peter, so they can be playmates for life. Check out Peter at: https://bit.ly/2SNXemK See more of Piper and her playmates on her foster's Instagram -- https://www.instagram.com/love_my_apa_fosters/ All APA! cats are fully vetted, spayed or neutered, and have updated vaccines and a microchip. Lifetime support is offered by our Cat Behavior Team. For further information or to meet Piper, please email adopt@austinpetsalive.org.
